Multiple Destinations Route Plan
Tony Li
Requirement
User always wants to visit several different places
at a time.
Get a route from airport and end with airport and
covering 6 tourist attractions:
A. Darling Harbour
B. The University of Sydney
C. Bondi Beach
D. QVB
E. Centennial Park
F. Sydney Opera House
Default Route plan
according to the order user assign, the total length of route is 51.8km
Best route
Reorganise points order, the total length of route is 37.8km
Comparison
Get a route from airport and end with airport
and covering 6 tourist attractions:
A. Darling Harbour
B. The University of Sydney
C. Bondi Beach
D. QVB
E. Centennial Park
F. Sydney Opera House
Default route: A-B-C-D-E-F, 1h21m, 51.8km
Best Route: B-D-A-F-C-E, 1h 4m, 37.8km
Essential problem
If we want to visit n points, to get the best
route, the time complexity is n!(n factorial)
e.g. if we want to visit 6 places, we need to calculate 6 * 5
* 4 * 3 * 2 * 1 = 720 routes in total to find the best route!
It is an NP complete problem
That is the reason why google map does not provide this
function now
Compromise
Genuine Solution
To get the best route covering 6 places, we need to calculate 720 times to get
the route with minimum length
Compromise
To get the relatively better route within limited times of calculation, we can
calculate out a route(using some tricks) with a length close to the minimum
length.
It is not necessarily the best route but very close to the best route, and whats
more, we wont calculate 720 times! Instead, only several times of calculation
are needed.
quality is sacrificed but only to a limited extent, so it is quite acceptable! And it
is very very fast!
Process Details
Group places according to distance
Calculate the internal best routes (more than one)
Merge groups to keep the sum of external distance
minimum
Keep merging until all places are in one group
Get the best internal routes from internal routes to make that
the sum (
distance of(origin, firstPlaceOfInternalRoute) +
distance of this internal route +
distance of(LastPlaceOfInternalRoute, destination))
is minimum
Flow Chart
Design Details
Use Highway Hierarchies Algorithm to
calculate each single route
Use Dijkstras Algorithm to calculate internal
routes
Use priorityQueue to store groups (ordered by
distance)
